Architecture plan for Issue #117: Render full post cards on the tag detail page and remove date cards

Module structure and file organization
- Primary change is isolated to `src/app/(public)/t/[slug]/page.tsx`, the public tag detail route.
- The tag detail route should own the page-level Prisma query, metadata generation, and rendering for posts belonging to the selected tag.
- Post-card presentation should match the existing public post-card pattern used by `src/app/(public)/page.tsx` and `src/app/(public)/s/[slug]/page.tsx`:
  - derive title from the first non-empty markdown line,
  - derive a plain-text excerpt from markdown,
  - show author, creation date, subspace, and tag chips,
  - link the card title to `/s/${post.subspace.slug}/${post.id}`.
- If implementation time allows, duplicate markdown helper functions can later be extracted into a small shared utility (for example `src/lib/post-preview.ts`) to reduce repeated logic across home, subspace, and tag pages. For this single issue, keeping the change scoped to the tag page is lowest risk.

Shared types and data shape
- The tag query must select complete post-card data from each `PostTag.post` relation:
  - `id`, `bodyMarkdown`, `createdAt`,
  - `author: { name, email }`,
  - `subspace: { name, slug }`,
  - `tags: [{ tag: { id, name, slug } }]` ordered by tag name.
- The tag-level `createdAt` and `updatedAt` fields are no longer needed for rendering once the date cards are removed.
- Metadata can continue to use `tag.name`, `tag.slug`, and `tag.posts.length`.

Dependencies between issues
- There is only one issue in this batch, so there are no cross-issue dependencies.
- The change depends only on the existing Prisma schema relationships between `Tag`, `PostTag`, `Post`, `User`, `Subspace`, and `Tag`.

Key design decisions
- Remove the entire "Tag details" section that renders Created/Updated cards, rather than hiding it with CSS, so the dates are absent from the accessible page structure.
- Render real post cards instead of post IDs to keep tag pages consistent with home and subspace pages.
- Preserve existing empty-state copy for tags with no posts.
- Use `prefetch={false}` consistently with existing public links in this app.
- Validate with lint/type checks and, if available, relevant tests after implementation.
